    ("Raspberry Pi Temperature and Humidity Sensor", "Read DHT11/DHT22 sensor data from Raspberry Pi and log to file.", ["Raspberry Pi", "DHT11 Temperature/Humidity Sensor", "Resistor 10kΩ (pull-up)", "Breadboard", "Female-female jumper wires"], ["DHT11 pin 1 to 3.3V (pin 1 on Pi)", "DHT11 pin 2 to GPIO 4 (pin 7)", "10kΩ pull-up resistor from pin 2 to 3.3V", "DHT11 pin 4 to GND (pin 6 on Pi)", "Install Adafruit_DHT: pip install Adafruit_DHT", "Write Python script to read sensor every 2 seconds", "Log data with timestamp to CSV file", "Plot data using matplotlib for visualization"], "DHT11 uses single-wire protocol to send temperature (°C) and humidity (%) data. Accuracy: ±2°C, ±5% RH. Range: 0-50°C, 20-80% RH. The 10kΩ pull-up keeps the data line HIGH. Read interval must be at least 1 second (DHT11 is slow). DHT22 provides better accuracy (±0.5°C, ±2% RH) and wider range."),
